{"source_key":"sha256-d0cd95f7d5f39f4b80f68f088e38f04c","record_index":48,"record_hash":"sha256:9f52d3c4295441ec4870f878c20586825b5691223231567a36a3c3785a745cfd","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:08:40.824Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 42a167\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 921\nOutput:\n     1\t# GitButler Cloud\n     2\t\n     3\tA private GitButler sync, backup, and takeover service built on top of\n     4\t[code.storage](https://code.storage).\n     5\t\n     6\tUsers sign up in the browser, approve a CLI device login, and then use\n     7\t`but-login`, `but-sync`, and `but-takeover` to move private GitButler refs\n     8\tbetween machines. The server proxies Git Smart HTTP to backing code.storage\n     9\trepositories using short-lived JWTs signed by your org private key.\n    10\t\n    11\tSee [`PLAN.md`](./PLAN.md) for the architecture writeup.\n    12\t\n    13\t## Stack\n    14\t\n    15\t- Next.js 15 (App Router, Node runtime) + TypeScript\n    16\t- Drizzle ORM + PlanetScale MySQL in every environment.\n    17\t- `iron-session` cookie auth, `bcryptjs` password hashes\n    18\t- `jose` for ES256 JWT signing\n    19\t- Rust CLI workspace for `but-login`, `but-sync`, `but-cloud`, and `but-takeover`\n    20\t- Tailwind CSS\n    21\t\n    22\t## Setup\n    23\t\n    24\t1. Copy and edit env:\n    25\t   ```bash\n    26\t   cp .env.example .env\n    27\t   # then set DATABASE_HOST, DATABASE_USERNAME, DATABASE_PASSWORD,\n    28\t   # PIERRE_ORG_NAME, PIERRE_PRIVATE_KEY, and SESSION_SECRET\n    29\t   ```\n    30\t2. Install + initialize the DB:\n    31\t   ```bash\n    32\t   pnpm install\n    33\t   pnpm db:push\n    34\t   ```\n    35\t3. Run it:\n    36\t   ```bash\n    37\t   pnpm dev\n    38\t   ```\n    39\t\n    40\t## Try it end-to-end\n    41\t\n    42\t```bash\n    43\t# 1. Start the local server and sign up at http://localhost:3000/signup\n    44\tpnpm dev\n    45\t\n    46\t# 2. In a Git repo, start CLI auth against local development and approve the printed URL\n    47\tcargo run -p but-cloud-cli --bin but-login -- --server http://localhost:3000\n    48\t\n    49\t# 3. Force-sync local branches and refs/meta/* to the cloud.\n    50\t#    The checkout gets its own gitbutler.cloudClientId in .git/config.\n    51\t#    Temporary wip commits are created during sync by default; pass --no-wip to disable.\n    52\tcargo run -p but-cloud-cli --bin but-sync\n    53\t\n    54\t# 4. Take over a branch from another synced client\n    55\tcargo run -p but-cloud-cli --bin but-takeover -- <client_id>/<branch>\n    56\t#    This stashes dirty work, unapplies other active GitButler branches,\n    57\t#    and picks cloud-only commits into the local target branch.\n    58\t\n    59\t# 5. Inspect synced cloud state\n    60\tcargo run -p but-cloud-cli --bin but-cloud -- clients\n    61\tcargo run -p but-cloud-cli --bin but-cloud -- branches\n    62\t```\n    63\t\n    64\tCloud projects are created on demand and backed by private code.storage repos.\n    65\t\n    66\tInstalled CLI binaries default to `https://gitbutler.dev`. Use\n    67\t`but-login --server http://localhost:3000` for local development.\n    68\t\n    69\tCLI credentials are stored per `server + user`. The global defaults are set by\n    70\tthe most recent successful login, and a repository can override either value:\n    71\t\n    72\t```bash\n    73\tgit config --local gitbutler.cloudServerUrl http://localhost:3000\n    74\tgit config --local gitbutler.cloudUser schacon2\n    75\t```\n    76\t\n    77\t## Layout\n    78\t\n    79\t```\n    80\tapp/\n    81\t  signup/, login/, cli/device/[code]/\n    82\t  settings/cloud/                   # CLI client revocation\n    83\t  api/auth/{signup,login,logout}/   # cookie-auth JSON APIs\n    84\t  api/cli/device/*                  # device auth flow\n    85\t  api/cloud/projects/resolve        # cloud project provisioning\n    86\t  api/cloud/git/[project]/*         # streaming Git Smart HTTP proxy\n    87\tcrates/but-cloud-cli/\n    88\t  src/bin/{but-cloud,but-login,but-sync,but-takeover}.rs\n    89\tlib/\n    90\t  db.ts            # Drizzle-backed query facade\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:08:40.824Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}